parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation or belt failure can lead to sudden blowouts, loss of control, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
Overinflation or incorrect tire pressure can lead to tire blowouts, tread separation, and loss of control, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
Defective tire design or manufacturing can lead to tire failures, blowouts, and accidents, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
A faulty fuel pump can cause the vehicle to jerk, lose power, and stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: especially on the highway. The engine may turn over but have no power and die immediately.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fractured fuel tank filler neck can cause fuel leakage, which can lead to fires, explosions, and accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leakage from the fuel tank filler neck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel injection system can cause the engine to hesitate, lose power, and stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: especially at low RPM or during slow turns. The vehicle may become unstable while cornering.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty fuel cut-off switch can cause the engine to stall, leading to a loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: and the fuel cut-off switch does not perform its function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A gasoline leak can cause fires, explosions, and accidents.
symptoms: and the engine may skip or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An improperly routed gas supply line can cause a gas leak, leading to fires, explosions, and accidents.
symptoms: The gas supply line is routed under the knife holder
which can cause it to be cut or weakened

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake caliper piston drag can cause the brakes to overheat, leading to a loss of braking force, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes fail to release on one or more wheels
the brakes drag until the brake calipers overheat
and the vehicle loses all braking force.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes go to the floor when deployed
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the pedal goes to the floorboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal assembly can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The rear brake pedal assembly is missing
the bolt that holds the pedal together is gone
and the pedal is hanging only from a line and spring.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lockup of the steering and brakes can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the brakes and steering wheel lock up
and the vehicle goes off the side of the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lockup of the rear wheel can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
